A vintage 1970s-style technical illustration showing a massive IBM Lotus Notes database depicted as an ornate filing cabinet with hundreds of tiny drawers, each drawer slightly open with streams of colorful data ribbons flowing out and transforming into various forms - pie charts, bar graphs, and spreadsheet grids floating in mid-air. The ribbons spiral and weave through the composition like a complex subway map. Warm sepia and amber tones dominate with pops of IBM blue and orange. The scene is set against a cream-colored paper background with subtle coffee stains and aged edges. Intricate cross-hatching and stippling techniques give depth to the mechanical cabinet, while the flowing data streams have a psychedelic, art nouveau quality with smooth gradients.
